      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 129: The registry key is built by concatenating `callId + \u0027:\u0027 + streamType`, but `forEach()` later splits on the first colon. Call IDs can contain arbitrary identifier formats, so a colon in the call ID corrupts iteration results and may make cleanup/debug tooling target the wrong call. Store a structured key instead of encoding two fields into one string.\n```suggestion\nusing Key \u003d std::pair\u003cstd::string, std::string\u003e;\nstruct KeyHash {\n    std::size_t operator()(const Key\u0026 key) const {\n        return std::hash\u003cstd::string\u003e{}(key.first) ^ (std::hash\u003cstd::string\u003e{}(key.second) \u003c\u003c 1);\n    }\n};\nstd::unordered_map\u003cKey, std::shared_ptr\u003cNetworkSimulator\u003e, KeyHash\u003e simulators_;\n```",
