      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 790: `onAudioCongestion()` holds `mutex_` while calling `setupVideoBitrateInfo()` and `setNewBitrate()`. Existing session methods commonly synchronize internally, so this risks self-deadlock or blocking RTP/RTCP work during bitrate reconfiguration. Compute the new bitrate under the lock if needed, release the lock, then call the bitrate setter outside the critical section.\n```suggestion\nunsigned int newBitrate;\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\n    auto now \u003d clock::now();\n    if (now - lastAudioQosReduction_ \u003c AUDIO_QOS_COOLDOWN)\n        return;\n    lastAudioQosReduction_ \u003d now;\n    setupVideoBitrateInfo();\n    auto oldBitrate \u003d videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent;\n    auto factor \u003d audioPacketLoss \u003e 10.0f ? 0.4f : audioPacketLoss \u003e 5.0f ? 0.5f : AUDIO_QOS_REDUCTION_FACTOR;\n    newBitrate \u003d std::max(static_cast\u003cunsigned int\u003e(std::lround(oldBitrate * factor)), videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateMin);\n    lastMediaRestart_ \u003d now;\n}\nsetNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n```",
